Nigeria will play Ukraine in an international friendly match this FIFA window. This is the first time both countries will ever face each other at senior level. Ukraine are billed to take on Lithuania in an Euro 2020 qualifier on Saturday in Vilnius before the game. The Super Eagles have not played any match, since they finished third at the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations. Kick off is 7.30pm West African time. Tuesday, August 10 Full time: Nigeria have been held to a 2-2 draw by Ukraine. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.